INSERT INTO `job_postings` VALUES (1,4259406253,'PHP Developer',1,'Europa, Mellem√∏sten og Afrika','Om jobbet\n\nWe are a trusted recruitment partner, committed to connecting talented professionals with leading organizations across the globe. We are hiring on behalf of an international software company seeking a skilled and motivated PHP Developer to join their growing development team. This is a full-time, remote opportunity open to professionals located within the EMEA region.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nAs a PHP Developer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining high-performance web applications and backend systems. You‚Äôll work closely with cross-functional teams including front-end developers, product managers, and QA engineers to build scalable and secure software solutions that align with business objectives.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nWrite clean, well-structured, and efficient PHP code.\nDevelop and maintain backend services and RESTful APIs.\nIntegrate third-party services and data sources.\nTroubleshoot, test, and maintain the core product software to ensure strong optimization and functionality.\nCollaborate with front-end developers and other team members to establish objectives and design cohesive, user-focused solutions.\nParticipate in code reviews and contribute to team knowledge sharing.\nStay current with industry trends and emerging technologies to suggest improvements and new approaches.\n\nRequirements\n\nProven experience as a PHP Developer with strong knowledge of object-oriented PHP programming.\nHands-on experience with PHP frameworks such as Laravel, Symfony, or CodeIgniter.\nSolid understanding of front-end technologies (HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript) is a plus.\nExperience working with MySQL or other relational databases.\nFamiliarity with version control systems like Git.\nExperience in developing and integrating RESTful APIs.\nStrong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.\nAbility to work independently in a remote environment and collaborate with distributed teams.\nExcellent English communication skills (written and spoken).\n\nWhat‚Äôs Offered\n\nFully remote role with flexible working hours within the EMEA region.\nOpportunity to work on innovative and global software projects.\nCollaborative, international team culture with a focus on growth and development.\nCompetitive salary and performance-based incentives.\n\nüì© Apply Today\n\nIf you\'re a passionate PHP Developer looking to work with a dynamic team on impactful digital products, we‚Äôd love to hear from you!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259406253/','2025-06-30',83,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-30 11:23:58','2025-06-30 11:23:58'),(2,4225170809,'Back End Developer',2,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nDescription\n\n√ònskeskyen / Gowish is looking for a Backend Developer to join our team. You will be working on the development of new features on the Platform within one of our dynamic Product Teams.\n\n\n\n\nAs a Backend Developer, you will be responsible for developing highly scalable and distributed backend services and infrastructure. You will work with a wide range of technologies, including Node.js, TypeScript, NestJS, GraphQL, Apollo, Cypher, SQL, Kafka, Kubernetes, Postgres and more. You will collaborate closely with frontend and app developers to create user, admin, and 3rd party-facing features, as well as contribute to the development of our infrastructure and other backend services.\n\n\n\n\nAbout us\n\nAt √ònskeskyen / GoWish, we are witnessing substantial growth with our innovative digital wish list application, which is gaining popularity both in Denmark and globally. As a Backend developer you will enhance our users feature set but also play a significant role in integrating and refining user satisfaction across the entire application lifecycle. This position offers a fantastic opportunity to refine your skills within our dynamic, cross-functional team and advance professionally in a forward-thinking environment.\n\n\n\n\nWorkplace \n\nOur office is located in the vibrant district of Nordhavn, Copenhagen, Denmark, where we foster an energetic work atmosphere. Our benefits include daily lunches, comprehensive health insurance, lively social events, and much more. This position is not remote. Relocation packages are not offered. \n\n\n\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDevelop highly scalable and distributed backend services\nWork in an agile team with a focus on quality and continuous delivery\nWork closely with product to understand the business needs and translate them into technical solutions\nWork closely with the frontend team to ensure a seamless integration of the frontend and backend\n\n\n\n\nQualifications\n\nStrong understanding of scalable and distributed systems\nExperience working with Node.js, TypeScript, NestJS, GraphQL, Kafka, Cypher\nStrong problem-solving skills and a willingness to take ownership of tasks\nA team player who is eager about sharing their knowledge and learning from others\nStrong communication skills and ability to decompose complex problems into manageable workable items\nFluent in English\n\n\n\n\nPreferred experience working with\n\nDistributed systems and Microservices\nGraph and SQL databases\nApollo Federated Graphs\nCloud infrastructure / Kubernetes\n\n\n\n\nSalary will be negotiated based on skills and experience.\n\n\n\n\nThe start date is ASAP and the position is permanent. This position will be based in Copenhagen, Denmark.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4225170809/','2025-05-30',100,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"Kubernetes\", \"Node.js\", \"OOP\", \"Python\", \"Webprogrammer\", \"Brugeroplevelse\", \"Skriftlig kommunikation\"]','2025-06-30 11:23:58','2025-06-30 11:23:58'),(3,4254867699,'Senior Developer',3,'K√∏benhavn og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nAbout SlideHub \n\nSlideHub is a fast-growing SaaS scale-up founded in 2016 by a team of Danish professionals. We provide clients access to a Presentation and Document Management platform that enables consultants, lawyers, marketing teams, sales organizations, and other business professionals to manage, access, and automate their presentations and documents. \n\n\n\n\nWe currently operate across four international offices with 45+ employees representing more than 12 different nationalities. While the company operates internationally, our product team is primarily based in Copenhagen, Denmark. \n\n\n\n\nThe Role \n\nAs a Senior Developer, you\'ll be focused on building, maintaining, testing, and scaling our SaaS platform alongside our core product team in Copenhagen. You\'ll drive client impact by developing new features and improving the scalability of existing features to serve our fast-growing user base. You\'ll work in close collaboration with three other developers, our full-time Product Designer, and our CEO/CTO, who oversees the product team. \n\n\n\n\nTechnology Stack \n\nBackend: \n\nPrimary: Laravel (latest version) \nSecondary: C# .NET (latest version) \n\nFrontend: \n\nVue3 \nTailwindCSS \n\nInfrastructure: \n\nCloud environment: AWS \nVersion control: GitHub \n\n\n\n\nDay-to-Day Responsibilities \n\nExecute and implement new product ideas based on detailed wireframes from our Product Designer \nImprove existing features based on client input (shared via customer success, sales, or directly from founders) \nShare ideas for solving client problems \nConduct pair programming sessions with other developers \nTrack and fix bugs and infrastructure bottlenecks across various monitoring systems \nParticipate in daily stand-ups \nHandle various ad-hoc problem-solving tasks \n\n\n\n\nLocation & Working Arrangements \n\nFully in-person role based in our Copenhagen office (5 days per week) \nOffice is centrally located in Copenhagen\'s Meatpacking District \n40 hours per week, including a daily 30-minute lunch break \nWorking hours: 8:00-9:00 AM to 4:00-5:00 PM CET \nWe provide flexibility to work from home for special occasions, but it\'s not the norm \n\n\n\n\nRequirements \n\nEssential Qualifications \n\nStrong verbal and written communication skills in English (all product work is conducted in English) \nMinimum 2-3 years of professional development experience \nGenuine passion for coding and takes pride in their craft \nExperience with Laravel and/or Vue \nSolid understanding of Git, version control, and PR reviews \nThrives in a high-output environment, doing work that directly impacts clients\' daily operations \nCan take ownership of feature development from design to production \nMotivated by working in-person with a small, high-output team and playing a big role in a fast-growing company \n\n\n\n\nHighly Desirable \n\nExperience with Laravel, C#, or Vue \nExperience from other SaaS startups or fast-moving agencies \n\nYou will thrive here if you enjoy hands-on coding, collaborating directly with stakeholders, and being part of a tight-knit team where your work has immediate impact. \n\n\n\n\nWhat We Offer \n\nIn addition to a competitive salary, you\'ll: \n\nPlay a key role in SlideHub\'s growth by building a product that thousands of professionals rely on each month \nBe part of an ambitious international company (12+ nationalities across 45+ people) \nJoin a fast-growing, profitable scale-up that isn\'t dependent on external funding \nMonthly Friday bar, bi-weekly breakfast, and a minimum of two annual social events (Summer and Christmas parties) \nNo overtime culture - we value sustainable productivity \n\n\n\n\nNext Steps \n\nWe\'re looking for a candidate to start in early October 2025 and will be conducting interviews on an ongoing basis. Ready to make an impact? We\'d love to hear from you.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4254867699/','2025-06-27',61,NULL,'[\".NET\", \"C\", \"C#\", \"Git\", \"JavaScript\", \"Programmering\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Versionskontrol\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Skriftlig kommunikation\"]','2025-