ial coatings R&D. To virtually visit the state-of-the-art labs that are at the center of the digitalization project, visit https://virtual.kt.dtu.dk/CoaST-labs/ . You will be at the heart of our ambitious project to develop a robust, user-friendly web interface designed to streamline laboratory workflows, experiment tracking, and data management. Working closely with scientists and users, you will ensure that our React-based platform meets their needs effectively, encouraging widespread adoption and making a tangible impact on research efficiency and collaboration. The digitalization project also includes integration with our maritime field test station in Hundested Harbour, supporting experimental activities under natural exposure conditions that complement laboratory-based studies.\n\nOur software ecosystem includes a React frontend connected via a FastAPI backend to a PostgreSQL database, all deployed seamlessly on Kubernetes using CI/CD pipelines. While your primary role will focus on front-end development, we encourage and support professional growth across the full stack, tailored specifically to your interests and skills.\n\nResponsibilities And Qualifications\n\nYou will be responsible for developing and refining a user-friendly React frontend, pivotal for ensuring laboratory researchers can efficiently specify experiments, manage and upload data, and streamline their workflow. You will collaborate closely with end-users from a highly international team with diverse academic and cultural backgrounds, gathering feedback to continuously improve usability and performance. You should enjoy open communication and value interdisciplinary teamwork. An understanding or background in chemical engineering would be advantageous, as it will facilitate effective communication and alignment with laboratory users.\n\nYour primary responsibilities will include:\n\n\nDesigning, developing, and maintaining a responsive and intuitive React-based frontend\nIntegrate the React frontend with REST APIs designed with FastAPI\nWriting and maintaining clear, professional documentation to ensure long-term maintainability and knowledge transfer\nCollaborating with lab users to clearly define their needs and continuously refine the user experience\nImplementing rigorous testing procedures to ensure software reliability and user satisfaction\nDeploying and managing applications using Kubernetes and CI/CD pipelines via GitLab\n\n\nEssential skills:\n\n\nSolid experience in React and JavaScript/TypeScript\nExperience in web application development and integrating React with REST APIs\nKnowledge of OpenAPI standards \nProficiency in Python for backend interactions and data processing\nFundamental knowledge of SQL databases\nFamiliarity with software testing methodologies and frameworks like Jest, Junit, pytest etc\nExperience with Git and containerized applications (Docker)\n\n\nAdditional beneficial skills include:\n\n\nBackground or basic understanding of chemical engineering or similar fields\nExperience with Kubernetes, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, or similar backend technologies\nAgile or Scrum project management practices\nSetting up and maintaining CI/CD pipelines for deployment in Kubernetes\nFamiliarity with authentication, authorization and user management.\n\n\nJoin us to create impactful software solutions that drive innovation and user engagement at the forefront of scientific research.\n\nFormal Qualifications\n\nYou should hold a relevant degree at the Bachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs level in computer science, software engineering, information technology, or a similar technical field. Applicants with degrees in other STEM disciplines and documented experience in frontend development are also encouraged to apply.\n\nWe offer\n\nDTU is a leading technical university globally recognized for the excellence of its research, education, innovation and scientific advice. We offer a rewarding and challenging job in an international environment. We strive for academic excellence in an environment characterized by collegial respect and academic freedom tempered by responsibility.\n\nSalary and appointment terms \n\nThe appointment will be based on the collective agreement with the Danish Confederation of Professional Associations (AC).\n\nApplication and contact\n\nPlease submit your online application no later than 16 July 2025 (23:59 Danish time). Open the ‚ÄúApply now‚Äù link, fill out the form and attach your motivated application, CV and exam certificates.\n\nIf you would like additional information about the position, please contact Associate Professor Jochen Dreyer ( jodre@kt.dtu.dk ).\n\nYou can read more about DTU Chemical Engineering and CoaST at www.kt.dtu.dk/english and https://www.kt.dtu.dk/research/coast, respectively. To take a virtual tour of the CoaST labs, visit https://virtual.kt.dtu.dk/CoaST-labs/.\n\nApplications received after the deadline will not be considered.\n\nAll interested candidates irrespective of age, gender, disability, race, religion or ethnic background are encouraged to apply. As DTU works with research in critical technology, which is subject to special rules for security and export control, open-source background checks may be conducted on qualified candidates for the position.\n\nThe Hempel Foundation Coatings Science and Technology Centre (CoaST) was established at the Technical University of Denmark, DTU, as per 1 January 2017, based on a generous donation by the Hempel Foundation. CoaST Research Centre supports the development, production and use of high-performance organic coatings. Working along the whole value chain, CoaST research activities cover organic, polymer-based coating technologies from raw materials over formulation, test and characterization to production and application.\n\nThe Department of Chemical and Biochemical Engineering at DTU is a leader in innovative teaching and research, built on core technical subjects and engineering scientific disciplines. The teaching and research cover separation processes, reaction engineering, dynamics and process regulation, process and facility planning, unit operations, heat transmission, fluid mechanics and applied thermodynamics. The Department enjoys very close relations with international partners, and especially a wide range of industrial companies. \n\nTechnology for people\n\nDTU develops technology for people. With our international elite research and study programmes, we are helping to create a better world and to solve the global challenges formulated in the UN‚Äôs 17 Sustainable Development Goals. Hans Christian √òrsted founded DTU in 1829 with a clear mission to develop and create value using science and engineering to benefit society. That mission lives on today. DTU has 13,500 students and 6,000 employees. We work in an international atmosphere and have an inclusive, evolving, and informal working environment. DTU has campuses in all parts of Denmark and in Greenland, and we collaborate with the best universities around the world.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4253125019/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\"Datalogi\", \"Frontend-udvikling\", \"Git\", \"JavaScript\", \"React.js\", \"SQL\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Databaser\", \"Kemiingeni√∏rarbejde\", \"Termodynamik\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(21,4251652650,'Technology Consultant',21,'K√∏benhavn og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nAre you passionate about designing and developing cutting-edge solutions that drive organizational success? Do you thrive in a dynamic environment where no two days are the same? We are looking for talents in both Copenhagen, Aarhus and Oslo.\n\n\n\n\nAt DYNACAP, we are looking for a talented Technology Consultant to join our team. In this role, you will take on diverse responsibilities, including solution design, development, configuration, testing, project management, and customer collaboration. You will have a direct impact on our clients‚Äô success while working closely with an ambi