iske Samarbejdsomr√•de','Om jobbet\n\nChief Technology Officer (CTO)\n\n Web3 / Crypto | Remote EU/ UK | ‚Ç¨250,000 to ‚Ç¨300,000 + equity\n\n\n\n\nWe are an ambitious Web3 venture dedicated to transforming how people engage with digital assets and decentralised technologies. Our platform provides millions of users with a secure and intuitive gateway to explore, manage and build within the blockchain and crypto landscape. Driven by innovation and a community-first approach, we are building the future of finance, ownership and identity in a decentralised world.\n\n\n\n\nWe are now looking for an experienced and visionary Chief Technology Officer (CTO) to lead our technology strategy, execution and innovation. This is an opportunity to guide the development of cutting-edge crypto and blockchain solutions while scaling a world-class engineering team.\n\n\n\n\nYour responsibilities\n\nSet and deliver the technology vision. Define the strategic direction of our technology architecture, infrastructure and development processes, ensuring scalability, security and alignment with our growth and product plans.\nDrive innovation. Stay ahead of emerging blockchain protocols, cryptographic developments and decentralised technologies, converting them into competitive advantages and product features.\nAlign technology with product. Work closely with product teams to deliver outstanding user experiences across our Web3 tools, wallets and decentralised applications.\nGrow and lead a high-performing engineering team. Attract, develop and retain exceptional talent while fostering a collaborative, inclusive and innovative culture focused on ownership and continuous improvement.\nCollaborate across the business. Partner with stakeholders in Product, Growth, Legal, Operations and Partnerships to ensure technology supports the wider business goals.\nEnsure security and resilience. Build and maintain robust security frameworks to safeguard user assets, ensure compliance and address emerging risks in the crypto space.\nManage resources and budgets. Allocate technology resources effectively to balance ambitious delivery with efficiency.\n\n\n\n\nWhat we are looking for\n\nProven leadership. At least five years of experience in senior technology positions, including at least two years in blockchain, Web3 or cryptocurrency organisations.\nDeep blockchain knowledge. Strong expertise in major blockchain ecosystems (such as Ethereum, Bitcoin and Layer 2 solutions), cryptography, smart contract security and consensus models.\nTrack record of delivery. Experience scaling technology platforms securely and reliably in a fast-moving environment, with a history of delivering complex technical projects.\nOpen-source mindset. A background in open-source development or community engagement is highly valued.\nStrategic and hands-on. Able to balance high-level technology strategy with the ability to engage in technical deep dives when necessary.\nClear communication. Comfortable explaining complex technical ideas to a wide range of audiences, including non-technical stakeholders.\nEmpowering leadership style. Committed to supporting and developing teams through coaching, feedback and inclusive practices.\n\n\n\n\nLocation and package\n\nThis is a remote-first position within Europe, with occasional travel to London for leadership meetings and team gatherings.\nSalary range is ‚Ç¨250,000 to ‚Ç¨300,000, with a generous equity or token package and a comprehensive benefits offering.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nApply now!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248877284/','2025-06-16',100,NULL,'[\"Cryptocurrency\", \"FinTech\", \"Team Development\", \"Technology Platforms\", \"Web3\", \"web3.js\"]','2025-06-30 11:32:25','2025-06-30 11:32:25'),(77,4239609620,'F√• et job i den h√∏jere sags tjeneste som sikkerhedsspecialist i PET',16,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nBr√¶nder du for IT-sikkerhed? Er du passioneret omkring s√•rbarhedsh√•ndtering? Er antivirus og certifikath√•ndtering din hjemmebane? Og ved du, hvad vi mener med MFA? S√• er det m√•ske dig, vi leder efter!\n\nBliv en del af holdet som sikrer PET‚Äôs IT-infrastruktur \n\nSom sikkerhedsspecialist i PET vil du f√• en central rolle i at skabe de mest sikre rammer for vores IT-systemer, data og applikationer. Du vi b√•de skulle bidrage med at tegne retningen for det fremtidige sikkerhedslandskab og samtidigt varetage de daglige driftsopgaver. Du vil blive brugt til sparring om risici og l√∏sninger, og du skal v√¶re ops√∏gende og sikre, at IT-sikkerheden l√∏bende bliver forbedret og tilpasset det aktuelle trusselsbillede.\n\nAf Andre Konkrete Opgaver Kan N√¶vnes\n\n\n Vulnerability management baseret p√• trusselsbilledet\n Implementering og l√∏bende drift af anti-virus l√∏sninger\n Teknisk analyse og r√•dgivning omkring sikkerhedsarkitekturen for eksisterende og nye IT-systemer\n SIEM-management og h√•ndtering af sikkerhedsh√¶ndelser\n H√•ndtering af certifikatudstedelser og efterf√∏lgende fejls√∏gning\n Implementering og drift af multifaktor godkendelsessystemer\n\n\nDu vil blive en del af PET‚Äôs IT-sektor, som leverer IT-services til hele organisationen. IT-sektoren best√•r af tre centre, et Infrastrukturcenter, et Applikationscenter og et Center for Digitale Services. Disse centre er yderligere opdelt i sektioner, hvor de faglige kompetencer er grupperet med hensyntagen til den bedst mulige underst√∏ttelse af leverancerne og faglige f√¶llesskaber.\n\nDu er l√¶renem og har gode samarbejdsevner\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at du er nysgerrig og har mod p√• at l√¶re nyt. Du er nysgerrig p√• nye teknologier og er drevet af at sikre et stabilt og sikkert IT-fundament for vores leverancer.\n\nVi forestiller os, at du har en relevant uddannelse inden for IT-sikkerhed eller IT-continuity og har flere √•rs praktisk erfaring med IT-sikkerhed i bred forstand. Derudover vil det v√¶re en fordel, at du har en relevant sikkerhedscertificering s√•som Security+, CySa+ fra CompTIA, SEC401, SEC501 fra SANS eller CISSP.\n\nSom sikkerhedsspecialist vil du sidde i en central rolle og have en bred ber√∏ringsflade. Derfor er det vigtigt, at du form√•r at skabe gode relationer, og at du har gode samarbejdsegenskaber og kan kommunikere trov√¶rdigt p√• flere niveauer. Dette er essentielt for kunne drive udviklingen, samt sikre at IT-sikkerhed bliver opfattet som en forretnings-enabler og ikke som en forhindring.\n\nI PET v√¶gter vi desuden visse personlige kompetencer h√∏jt. Det er kompetencer, som vi mener, er essentielle for alle PET-ansatte uanset faglig baggrund. Det g√∏r vi, fordi det er vigtigt for os, at vi finder det rette match. Du kan l√¶se om kompetencerne her www.pet.dk/job.\n\nF√• en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag\n\nPET er en stor IT-arbejdsplads. Her arbejder Java-udviklere, infrastrukturspecialister, netv√¶rksteknikere, autodidakte hackere, firewallspecialister og mange andre med en baggrund inden for IT. Nogle har valgt PET for at arbejde med store og komplekse opgaver. Andre faldt for, at vi selv designer mange af vores l√∏sninger fra bunden, udvikler og implementerer dem. Vores kollegaer skal bruge vores arbejde, og vi er med fra start til slut. Endelig har mange af os valgt jobbet for at arbejde med en sag, der er st√∏rre end profit og timefakturering. Vi har et h√∏jere form√•l.\n\nVores arbejdsplads er som ingen andre. Vores opgave er at forebygge, efterforske og modvirke trusler mod friheden, demokratiet og sikkerheden i det danske samfund. Dette stiller h√∏je krav til vores IT-l√∏sninger, datakvalitet og ikke mindst passionerede og kompetente medarbejdere. Vi har en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag, og det kan du ogs√• f√•.\n\nAns√¶ttelsesforhold\n\nDu kan l√¶se mere om hele PET‚Äôs ans√¶ttelsesproces p√• www.pet.dk/job.\n\nAns√¶ttelsesstart pr. 1. november2025\n\nDit arbejdssted bliver p√• Klausdalsbrovej 1 i S√∏borg, lige ved siden af Buddinge station. Her har vi bl.a. et gratis, veludstyret fitnesscenter, mange sociale arrangementer som sommerfest og DHL samt en aktiv personaleforening, hvorigennem du kan opn√• diverse fordele og rabatter. Derudover f√•r du fleksible arbejdstider, betalt frokostpause og en ledelse der har fokus p√• balancen mellem arbejde og fritid.\n\nHar du en akademisk baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til de til enhver tid g√¶ldende aftaler mellem Finansministeriet og Akademikernes Centralorganisation. Har du en anden uddannelsesm√¶ssig baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til den til enhver tid g√¶ldende organisationsaftale for kontorfunktion√¶rer i staten mellem Finansministeriet og HK/STAT samt OAO-S-f√¶llesoverenskomst. Alternativt bliver du ansat p√• anden relevant overenskomst.\n\nEt ans√¶ttelsesforhold i PET skal behandles med diskretion, hvilket du som ans√∏ger skal v√¶re opm√¶rksom p√•. Det betyder, at du som udgangspunkt godt kan fort√¶lle t√¶tte og fortrolige relationer, som du har tillid til, at du har s√∏gt en stilling i PET, men ikke hvad jobbet indeb√¶rer.\n\nDet er en foruds√¶tning for ans√¶ttelse i PET, at du kan sikkerhedsgodkendes, ligesom du skal kunne opretholde sikkerhedsgodkendelsen gennem hele din ans√¶ttelse. Som sikkerhedsgodkendt forventes det, at du er s√¶rlig opm√¶rksom p√• din tavshedspligt i forhold til klassificeret information.\n\nYderligere information\n\nVi forventer at p√•begynde samtaler i uge 33. Grundet sommerferie m√• du som ans√∏ger forvente lidt l√¶ngere svartid, fra du har s√∏gt stillingen, til du h√∏rer fra os.\n\nDu er altid meget velkommen til at kontakte os p√• hverdage p√• mail hr-rekruttering@politi.dk eller p√• telefon +45 24 62 18 45, hvis du har sp√∏rgsm√•l til stillingen, PET som arbejdsplads eller lignende.\n\nN√•r du s√∏ger en stilling hos PET, giver du lov til, at vi m√• indhente dit CPR-nummer via CPR-registeret med henblik p√• identifikation af dig i forbindelse med rekrutteringsprocessen. Vi indhenter dit CPR-nummer, s√• vi sikkert kan fremsende relevante og n√∏dvendige dokumenter til dig via Digital Post.\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at PET afspejler den mangfoldighed, som vi arbejder for. Derfor opfordrer vi alle interesserede, uanset k√∏n, alder, religion, seksualitet og etniske tilh√∏rsforhold til at s√∏ge stillingen.\n\nTr√¶d ind i en lukket verden, der √•bner nye d√∏re, hvor vi udvikler os, tr√¶ner og bygger videre p√• det, vi kan. Om vi udvikler nye systemer, analyserer data eller finjusterer fodstillingen til skydetr√¶ning, s√• er vi altid p√• t√¶erne. Det skaber gode muligheder for, at du kan rykke dig med os, vokse med opgaverne og √•bne nye d√∏re i dit arbejdsliv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4239609620/','2025-06-24',22,NULL,'[\"Antivirus\", \"Driftsledelse\", \"IT Security Operations\", \"Informationssikkerhed\", \"Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)\", \"Sikkerhedsrisici-ledelse\"]','2025-06-30 11:32:25','2025-06-30 11:32:25'),(78,4160224550,'Senior Full Stack Engineer',56,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nJob Description\n\nMost companies run through gigantic spreadsheets twice a month to invoice their customers. This is boring and mistakes happen. Do you want to help solve billing once and for all?\n\nWe are a profitable startup, and we are expanding. You won\'t have to deal with any legacy code, no decisions made 10 years ago holding you back, just pure speed. We are looking for a Senior Full Stack Engineer. You are part of the entire process from understanding the foundational problem, designing the solution, and pushing a product out.\n\nYou will work closely with everyone in Proper and our customers. We build our products through a process inspired by experiments. First, we test ideas, and product market fit with prototypes, interviews, or other ways. Once we understand the job to be done and the market, we either move on to a prototyping stage with more software or proceed directly to writing code. This approach allows us to move fast, stay flexible, and confidently deliver high-quality products.\n\nWhat\'s the job:\n\n\nHelp us find product-market fit with the new product.\nWork in a small, focused product team with our co-founder.\nPut together mockups, proof-of-concepts, iterate and ship fast.\nBe part of choosing the right frameworks and technologies for the job.\nLots of focus time without rigid processes.\n\n\nWhat we are looking for:\n\n\nStrong technical skills with a flare for building products and solving real, painful problems for our customers.\nFocus on customer needs rather than following a detailed specification.\nEnjoy working independently and driving things forward on your own.\nExcel in working with the entire stack; frontend, backend and cloud infrastructure.\nExperience working on multiple different products from your past.\nStrong communication skills and fluent in English.\nLocated in the Copenhagen area.\n\n\nTechnologies we use:\n\n\nJava, AWS (SQS, SNS, DynamoDB, Lambda, CDK)\nTypeScript, React, Next.js, Tailwind\nEvent-driven architecture\nDomain-driven Design concepts\nMacOS\n\n\nWe don‚Äôt expect you to be an expert in all of these technologies, however, we want you to be up and running fast, so you should have worked professionally with Java, are familiar with the AWS ecosystem and have solid experience with building React apps.\n\nBenefits:\n\n\nBenefit from our warrant program, giving you a stake in the company\'s success.\nWork in a unique office in central Copenhagen.\nEnjoy a delicious and complimentary lunch.\nSupport from your manager with weekly 1:1s.\n\n\nWhy Proper?\n\nWe impact thousands of people every day significantly by designing a smarter billing solution. You won‚Äôt be burdened by operations and legacy. And your contributions will actually make a big difference. Expect occasional chaos as we explore new grounds and solve problems. Support in redesigning financial processes to make them efficient and user-friendly. Gain experience with different technologies and join us on our mission to change how businesses work from the inside out.\n\nJoin us:\n\nAt Proper, you help rethink financial processes with new technology.\n\nWe\'re looking for people, not bullet points. Do you not fit the description perfectly? Don\'t let that hold you back. Let your skills and passion stand out, especially if your career has taken some interesting twists and turns. We thrive on diverse viewpoints and rigorous thinkers who aren\'t afraid to challenge assumptions.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4160224550/','2025-03-02',NULL,NULL,'[\"AngularJS\", \"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Full-Stack Development\", \"HTML5\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"React.js\", \"Stak\", \"TypeScript\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\"]','2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(79,4254880439,'ServiceNow Consultant/Developer - 3 months+ - Europe',60,'Det Europ√¶iske √òkonomiske Samarbejdsomr√•de','Om jobbet\n\nServiceNow Consultant/Developer - 3 months+ - Europe \n\n\n\n\nFor a multi-national ServiceNow Partner we are looking for several ServiceNow Consultants/Developers to design, configure, and enhance digital workflows across HR Service Delivery (HRSD), Customer Service Management (CSM), and ServiceNow AI features. \n\n\n\n\nYou are able to work anywhere in Europe, but preferably Spain, France, Bulgaria.\n\nEnglish language ok, with local language a bonus\n\n\n\n\nThe Role\n\nDesign and develop solutions in HRSD, CSM, or AI/ML-enabled ServiceNow apps (e.g., Virtual Agent, Predictive Intelligence).\nCustomize forms, flows, UI policies, business rules, and integrations (REST/SOAP).\nTranslate business requirements into technical specs and user stories.\nCollaborate with functional consultants, testers, and project managers in Agile delivery.\nMaintain platform integrity through scalable, secure configurations and code.\nProvide input on roadmap planning, upgrades, and new features.\n\n\n\n\nYour Skills & Experience\n\n3+ years of hands-on ServiceNow development \nExcellent customer facing and stakeholder management skills, focus on your consultative approach to customers\nStrong experience with at least one: HRSD, CSM, ServiceNow AI\nExperience with Agile/Scrum delivery (e.g., Jira, sprint planning).\nNice to have: ServiceNow CSA, Certified Implementation Specialist \n\n\n\n\nIf you are interested, please apply with your latest CV and best number to contact you on. chloe.carr@next-ventures.com','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4254880439/','2025-06-27',98,NULL,'[\"HR Service Delivery\", \"Kundeserviceadministration\", \"ServiceNow\"]','2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(80,4240069240,'Fullstack Typescript Engineer (Copenhagen)',61,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nResponsibly üåçüå±\n\n\n\n\nResponsibly is a sustainability tech start-up with a vision of making every purchase in the world responsible.\n\n\n\n\nWe\'re founded by serial entrepreneurs with previous successes like Ofload, Dixa, Neurons, and more, and are funded by some of Europe\'s top VCs and angels.\n\n\n\n\nWe‚Äôre at the most exciting part of our journey (yet!) where the product is being picked up by some of the biggest companies out there, and we have an incredibly exciting roadmap ahead of us! ü§ò\n\n\n\n\nLet‚Äôs change the world together üéØ\n\n\n\n\nIf you already know why sustainable procurement is sexy, then skip this section, if not, read on!\n\n\n\n\nLook, you probably already know that there are not many bigger problems out there than the climate, but did you know that more than 40% of global emissions, or really any ESG issue, are directly or indirectly impacted by procurement? That‚Äôs because companies have an incredible amount of power (‚Äòpurchasing power‚Äô) when selecting and managing suppliers, so if we can put sustainability on every supplier scorecard out there, we really can change the world.\n\n\n\n\nBut it‚Äôs hard! A company will have anywhere from 100 - 100,000 suppliers and analyzing each of their sustainability efforts is an impossible task, and most ESG ratings suck.\n\n\n\n\nThat‚Äôs what we‚Äôre trying to change. Responsibly\'s ai-powered due diligence engine automates the due diligence on every supplier across every single esg data point on your suppliers (from risk and violations to positive actions), and turns that into insights to ultimately help companies build more sustainable supply chains.\n\n\n\n\nPretty cool right?\n\n(yes, this dorky description was indeed written by an overly excited founder‚Ä¶)\n\n\n\n\nBuild next gen products using next gen technologies üåü\n\n\n\n\nWe‚Äôre growing our Fullstack engineering team to craft the next-generation sustainability due diligence platform.\n\n\n\n\nAt Responsibly, you‚Äôll work on a Next.js 15 app leveraging the latest in server actions, server components, and cutting-edge serverless architectures. This is your chance to build dynamic, high-performance applications with modern tools like TypeScript, PostgreSQL, and AI integrations. Every day brings exciting challenges where you can push boundaries, innovate with the latest technologies, and create impactful solutions for a more sustainable future.\n\n\n\n\nAlso, we don‚Äôt just leverage AI for our product, but we also want to build a next generation engineering team, where you‚Äôre not only encouraged, but expected to adopt the latest technologies in your engineering.\n\n\nTasks\n\n\nWhat you‚Äôll be doing üôå\n\n\n\n\n\nTaking operational responsibility for the code that you write throughout the entire software development life cycle\n\n\nWorking on production code, from customer related operations to bug fixing\n\n\nWorking closely with your team on designing new features and seeing them through to completion\n\n\nBeing part of building and evolving our services and infrastructure to stay ahead of our growth curve\n\n\nBuilding exciting new features for our customers and business partners\n\n\nHelping take conceptual ideas and turn them into production-ready scalable features\n\n\nBeing a big part of finding the best possible solutions to our daily challenges\n\n\n\nRequirements\n\n\nAbout you üòé\n\n\n\n\n\nWhere you lack experience, you make up for it with passion, talent and dedication; if you‚Äôre straight out of school, you can still convince us if you can demonstrate this. But generally:\n\n\nYou have solid experience with TypeScript and a proven ability to work with modern frameworks like Next.js, including server actions, server components, and API routes.\n\n\nYou have experience, desire and passion for integrating cutting-edge AI tools and working with LLMs (e.g., OpenAI, HuggingFace).\n\n\nYou are experienced in building REST APIs and have an understanding of designing, debugging, and deploying scalable web applications.\n\n\nYou have some hands-on experience with PostgreSQL or other relational databases and understand how to design efficient, maintainable database schemas.\n\n\nYou have experience with, or a desire to work with serverless architectures, including technologies like AWS Lambda.\n\n\nYou‚Äôre comfortable working with AWS services or similar cloud providers. \n\n\nYou have experience with web scraping tools and techniques.\n\n\nYou value writing clean, testable, and maintainable code and have a track record of doing so.\n\n\n\nBenefits\n\n\nYour benefits ü§©\n\n\n\n\n\nCompetitive salary & opportunity for ESOP participation\n\n\nOnsite in our awesome office in Islands Brygge, but flexibility around hours and remote working.\n\n\nOffice located in Islands Brygge, close to the water, with awesome lunch, great coffee, and the obligatory ping pong table. \n\n\nLots of fun, like our annual company event or Friday bars!\n\n\n\n\n\nStill need to be convinced? ü§î\n\n\n\n\n\nIt‚Äôs the opportunity to join an early-stage tech & social impact company on an incredible journey. You‚Äôll have the independence and space to release your creativity\n\n\nYou\'ll become a vital member of the team, and your efforts will have a direct impact on the Responsibly‚Äôs success. \n\n\nYou‚Äôll be part of a dynamic company with enthusiastic and highly talented teammates from all backgrounds and countries ‚Äì always ready to share knowledge, support, and a beer! Successes are always shared together\n\n\nWe will offer you strong personal and professional development opportunities in a dynamic and high-growth environment ‚Äì we want to take you from good to great. \n\n\nWe\'ll encourage you to push boundaries and be the greatest version of yourself by providing the balance of freedom and structure with a good dose of fun.\n\n\nWe have fun and we make an impact - life is about more than work!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4240069240/','2025-06-09',100,NULL,'[\"AngularJS\", \"Full-Stack Development\", \"HTML5\", \"PostgreSQL\", \"REST APIs\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"TypeScript\", \"Webprogrammer\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"REST\"]','2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(81,4128456601,'Backend Lead Engineer',57,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nJoin one of Denmark\'s fastest growing B2B startups and be part of a company that values its customers so much that our median customer support ticket response time is 21 seconds!\n\nResights began with a vision to consolidate real estate data onto a single platform - to save time and enhance decision making. No more cluttered spreadsheets or gut feelings üòµ‚Äçüí´ Since then, we have through an unusually close relationship to customers, developed the platform immensely. Today, the platform caters for many different use cases and is way more than a database. For example, you can find new investment properties, analyse cities and automate direct mails to property owners. The common thread is real estate data and how we can enable our customers to make more business.\n\nSo, in a nutshell, that‚Äôs Resights. But in truth, what really defines us are the 45 people behind our software. A collection of nerdy team players who, in three years, have built one of fastest growing startups in Denmark, boasting over 1000 customers. Even with healthy finances and no big VC check. Most importantly, we have had a lot of fun, because that\'s truly a part of our DNA (read our culture memo here) üß¨\n\nWant to get a glimpse of what we are working on and what stack we use? \n\nOur tech stack consists of, backend services and workflows written in Python, and our APIs serve JSON over HTTP. Everything is deployed to Kubernetes, using ArgoCD, and our data workflows are orchestrated by Argo Workflows. The frontend is a SPA written with VueJS. Finally, everything is hosted on AWS. Besides that, our engineers know their way around document-oriented databases (Elasticsearch) and SQL databases (PostgreSQL).\n\nWe\'ve recently released our API and Data Catalogue, allowing anyone to access all public data through just one integration. We are even collaborating with Snowflake on our API services now. How cool is that?\n\nYou love\n\n\nThat deadlines can change.\nWorking on multiple problems at the same time.\nChanging your focus completely even though you‚Äôve been heads down in a complex project for 5 weeks. How delightful.\nFinding the root cause of customer needs before diving into solutions.\nArchitecting solutions that are meant to work for a long time.\nChallenging status quo and what can be done.\nThat the best argument wins, no matter who it comes from.\nAsking for forgiveness rather than permission.\n\n\nYou are not comfortable with\n\n\nBeing a specialist, because that puts you too much into one bucket. You like more buckets.\nProcesses that are set in stone.\nSporadic communication. Because you know that clear and frequent communication solves many issues.\nMaking a solution before you understand the problem. But you also know when to dive into solution land and iterate enough to find the best solution.\nFocusing on output as a driver for growth (psst, we value outcome over output).\n\n\nWhat You Will Be Doing\n\n\nLeading our backend engineering team of 4 talented engineers\nChallenge how we work and mentor your engineering teams\nArchitect new features, or re-architect existing features for the next step\nGet your hands on the codebase - this is more a hands-on opportunity than pure management\nWork with databases like Postgres, Elasticsearch, and Neo4j\nProgram in Python, and work with our infrastructure hosted in AWS using Kubernetes and Terraform\nDeep-dive into Danish public data-models and become an expert in Real Estate data\nUse your creativity to transform plain and boring data into insightful solutions loved by our clients\n\n\nWhat You Will NOT Be Doing\n\n\nFixing an old legacy codebase that has been pushed to it\'s limit. Refactors are needed sometimes, but we appreciate to do them on an ongoing basis\n\n\nAbout You\n\nWe don\'t really believe in a long list of requirements. We imagine that you have previous experience as a Software Engineer, familiar with our tech stack, have slightly touched upon mentoring other engineers, and that you are fluent in Danish. We are not looking for a specific number of years, but rather the impact you‚Äôve had. That\'s also why we highly emphasize that you attach proof of work üôå\n\nIf the basic requirements are in place, then the most important thing is an assessment of your talents and skills. To limit human bias, we make use of a digital tool and a realistic engineering case to assess this. We believe this is the fairest way to recruit new people, so it\'s not about anything other than your ability to solve the tasks and have a workday you don\'t want to leave from. Quite simple.\n\n\nBonus Points\nExperience working with non-trivial amounts of data. You can move it around, massage it and love it\nExperience with the operational side of software development. You know what it takes to run software in production.\nHands-on experience with Kubernetes, and related tools: Kustomize, Helm, ArgoCD.\nExperience with containerization. You can write a multi-stage dockerfile, and debug problems.\nExperience with writing high quality tests.\nExperience with FastAPI and poetry','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4128456601/','2025-01-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"JavaScript\", \"Kubernetes\", \"OOP\", \"PostgreSQL\", \"Python\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Databaser\", \"JSON\"]','2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(82,4209727348,'Senior Frontend Web Developer',62,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nSenior Frontend Udvikler til Lasso X\n\n\n\n\nVil du v√¶re med til at transformere hvordan virksomheder f√•r nye kunder? Lasso X s√∏ger en Senior Frontend Udvikler med k√¶rlighed til React og TypeScript til at st√• i spidsen for udvikling af vores salgsv√¶rkt√∏j til virksomheder.\n\n\n\n\nOm Lasso X\n\nVi er en k√∏benhavnsk virksomhed i rivende udvikling. Med 11 √•r p√• bagen og 18 passionerede medarbejdere er vi f√∏rende I at g√∏re vores kunder datadrevne ved hj√¶lp af information om virksomheder og erhvervslivet. Vi drives af iv√¶rks√¶tter√•nd og v√¶rner om det sociale sammenhold. Vores centrale beliggenhed ved Toldboden i K√∏benhavn danner rammen om et fagligt inspirerende milj√∏.\n\n\n\n\nJobbet\n\nSom Senior Frontend Udvikler vil du:\n\n\n\n\n¬∑ Lede frontend-udviklingen af vores nye B2B leadgenereringsprodukt\n\n¬∑ Arbejde t√¶t sammen med en backend-udvikler og designer\n\n¬∑ Formidle data p√• en intuitiv og brugervenlig m√•de, med dit flair for design og god UX\n\n¬∑ Skabe moderne web-applikationer, der er b√•de √¶stetiske og effektive\n\n¬∑ V√¶re en del af et dedikeret udviklingsteam med CTO\'en som direkte leder\n\n\n\n\nVi er n√∏rder omkring detaljerne og produktet i det hele taget, og elsker at g√∏re komplekse ting simple. Du vil blive inspireret af knivskarpe og dygtige kollegaer, der s√¶tter kvalitet i h√∏js√¶det. Dit arbejde vil lande direkte i h√¶nderne p√• vores kunder, som sp√¶nder fra Danmarks st√∏rste firmaer og kendte brands, til hundredvis af sm√• og mellemstore virksomheder i n√¶sten alle brancher.\n\n\n\n\nDin profil\n\n¬∑ Dokumenteret erfaring som senior frontend-udvikler\n\n¬∑ Ekspertise i TypeScript og React\n\n¬∑ Flair for design og god UX\n\n¬∑ Gode samarbejdsevner og erfaring med at arbejde i tv√¶rfaglige teams\n\n¬∑ Trives i et socialt og fagligt √•bent milj√∏.\n\n\n\n\nVi tilbyder\n\n¬∑ Konkurrencedygtig l√∏n, der matcher din senior profil\n\n¬∑ Et dynamisk arbejdsmilj√∏ i hjertet af K√∏benhavn\n\n¬∑ Nyudvikling i over 80% af dit arbejde.\n\n¬∑ Udvikling af et produkt, der bruges af f√∏rende virksomheder.\n\n¬∑ Et fedt arbejdsmilj√∏ med h√∏jt til loftet og dedikerede kolleger.\n\n\n\n\nEr du interesseret i at tage en snak med os omkring jobbet, s√• send os din ans√∏gning.\n\nAns√¶ttelsestart hurtigst muligt.\n\n\n\n\nVi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra dig!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4209727348/','2025-04-30',100,NULL,NULL,'2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(83,4250818671,'Bliv lognings- og overv√•gningsspecialist i PET og f√• et job med et h√∏jere form√•l',16,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nMotiveres du af at designe og implementere observability l√∏sninger? Br√¶nder du for at modellere serviceorienteret overv√•gning af IT-infrastruktur og applikationer, samt udstille relevante dashboards? Anerkender du vigtigheden af opsamling og lagring af system logs, herunder compliancekrav? S√• er du m√•ske vores nye kollega\n\nBliv en del af holdet som sikrer stabil drift af PET‚Äôs IT-infrastruktur \n\nSom logning- og overv√•gningsspecialist i PET vil du f√• en central rolle i at s√¶tte retningen for vores lognings- og overv√•gningssystemer. Du skal deltage i implementeringen af nye systemer, samtidig med at du f√•r til opgave, at beskrive behov for logning og overv√•gning af systemer og applikationer samt konfigurere disse i systemerne.\n\nI forhold til systemoverv√•gning vil du, i samarbejde med dine kollegaer, udstille relevant data i serviceorienterede dashboards, som skal sikre rettidig og korrekt reaktion p√• events og samtidig v√¶re beslutningsunderst√∏ttende for blandt andet ledelsen.\n\nAf Konkrete Opgaver Kan N√¶vnes\n\n\n Udvikle, implementere og drifte lognings- og overv√•gningsl√∏sninger\n Konsolidere og integrere lognings- og overv√•gningsl√∏sninger\n Drive modningsprocessen i forhold til hvordan systemer overv√•ges, og hvordan data udstilles\n Bist√• med loganalyse\n R√•dgive kollegaer om instrumentering af systemer, s√• de overv√•ges bedst muligt\n\n\nDu bliver en del af PET‚Äôs IT-sektor, som tilsammen leverer IT-services til hele organisationen. IT-sektoren best√•r af tre centre: et infrastrukturcenter, et applikationscenter og et center for processer og support. Disse centre er yderligere opdelt i sektioner, hvor de faglige kompetencer er grupperet med hensyntagen til den bedst mulige underst√∏ttelse af leverancerne og faglige f√¶llesskaber. Vores kultur er baseret p√• samarbejde, tillid og ansvarlighed.\n\nDu er l√¶renem og har gode samarbejdsevner\n\nVi ser gerne, at du har en relevant uddannelse inden for IT og har flere √•rs praktisk erfaring inden for enten lognings- eller overv√•gningsomr√•det. Du har formentlig arbejdet med drift af infrastruktur og er fortrolig med diverse operativsystemer og infrastruktur-komponenter. Det er en fordel, hvis du har erfaring med b√•de enterprise og open source-l√∏sninger, og har bygget full-stack l√∏sninger til b√•de monitorering og logning med fokus p√• h√∏j tilg√¶ngelighed i et 24/7 milj√∏.\n\nKompetencer og erfaring med scripting og automatisering er en fordel, ligesom kendskab til ITIL vil v√¶re et godt fundament.\n\nI PET v√¶gter vi desuden visse personlige kompetencer h√∏jt. Det er kompetencer, som vi mener, er essentielle for alle PET-ansatte uanset faglig baggrund. Det g√∏r vi, fordi det er vigtigt for os, at vi finder det rette match. Du kan l√¶se om kompetencerne her www.pet.dk/job.\n\nF√• en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag\n\nVores arbejdsplads er som ingen andre. Vores opgave er at forebygge, efterforske og modvirke trusler mod friheden, demokratiet og sikkerheden i det danske samfund. Dette stiller h√∏je krav til vores IT-l√∏sninger, datakvalitet og ikke mindst passionerede og kompetente medarbejdere. Derfor er vi en bred r√¶kke af IT-specialister. Nogle har valgt PET for at arbejde med store og komplekse opgaver. Andre faldt for, at vi selv designer mange af vores l√∏sninger fra bunden, udvikler og implementerer dem. Vores kollegaer skal bruge vores arbejde, og vi er med fra start til slut. Endelig har mange af os valgt jobbet for at arbejde med en sag, der er st√∏rre end profit og timefakturering. Vi har et h√∏jere form√•l.\n\nSom lognings- og overv√•gningsspecialist i PET bliver du en del af en hverdag, der er pr√¶get af opgaver, som ikke findes andre steder, og hver dag byder p√• nye udfordringer, som ikke fandtes i g√•r. Vi har en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag, og det kan du ogs√• f√•.\n\nAns√¶ttelsesforhold\n\nAns√¶ttelsesstart pr. 1 november 2025. Grundet sommerferie kan der g√• et stykke tid, f√∏r du h√∏rer fra os. Vi h√•ber meget, at du vil v√¶re t√•lmodig med os. Vi forventer at p√•begynde samtaler i uge 35.\n\nDu kan l√¶se mere om hele PET‚Äôs ans√¶ttelsesproces p√• www.pet.dk/job.\n\nEt ans√¶ttelsesforhold i PET skal behandles med diskretion, hvilket du som ans√∏ger skal v√¶re opm√¶rksom p√•. Det betyder, at du som udgangspunkt godt kan fort√¶lle t√¶tte og fortrolige relationer, som du har tillid til, at du har s√∏gt en stilling i PET, men ikke hvad jobbet indeb√¶rer.\n\nDet er en foruds√¶tning for ans√¶ttelse i PET, at du kan sikkerhedsgodkendes til yderst hemmeligt, ligesom du skal kunne opretholde sikkerhedsgodkendelsen gennem hele din ans√¶ttelse. Som sikkerhedsgodkendt forventes det, at du er s√¶rlig opm√¶rksom p√• din tavshedspligt i forhold til klassificeret information.\n\nHar du en akademisk baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til de til enhver tid g√¶ldende aftaler mellem Finansministeriet og Akademikernes Centralorganisation. Har du en anden uddannelsesm√¶ssig baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til den til enhver tid g√¶ldende organisationsaftale for kontorfunktion√¶rer i staten mellem Finansministeriet og HK/STAT samt OAO-S-f√¶llesoverenskomst. Alternativt bliver du ansat p√• anden relevant overenskomst.\n\nDit arbejdssted bliver p√• Klausdalsbrovej 1 i S√∏borg, lige ved siden af Buddinge station, hvor b√•de S-tog og bus k√∏rer lige til d√∏ren. I PET arbejder vi p√• interne systemer og med fortrolige opgaver, og derfor m√∏der vi ogs√• p√• arbejde hver dag for at l√∏se vores opgaver.\n\nYderligere information\n\nDu kan l√¶re meget mere om PET som arbejdsplads p√• www.pet.dk/job, hvor du bl.a. kan l√¶se mere om alle de fagligheder, der arbejder i PET og deres hverdag. Du kan ogs√• lytte til vores podcastserie ‚ÄôTjenesten og truslerne‚Äô.\n\nDu er ogs√• altid meget velkommen til at kontakte os p√• hverdage p√• mail hr-rekruttering@politi.dk eller p√• telefon +45 24 62 18 45, hvis du har sp√∏rgsm√•l til stillingen, PET som arbejdsplads eller lignende.\n\nN√•r du s√∏ger en stilling hos PET, giver du lov til, at vi m√• indhente dit CPR-nummer via CPR-registeret med henblik p√• identifikation af dig i forbindelse med rekrutteringsprocessen. Vi indhenter dit CPR-nummer, s√• vi sikkert kan fremsende relevante og n√∏dvendige dokumenter til dig via Digital Post.\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at PET afspejler den mangfoldighed, som vi arbejder for. Derfor opfordrer vi alle interesserede, uanset k√∏n, alder, religion, seksualitet og etniske tilh√∏rsforhold til at s√∏ge stillingen.\n\nTr√¶d ind i en lukket verden, der √•bner nye d√∏re, hvor vi udvikler os, tr√¶ner og bygger videre p√• det, vi kan. Om vi udvikler nye systemer, analyserer data eller finjusterer fodstillingen til skydetr√¶ning, s√• er vi altid p√• t√¶erne. Det skaber gode muligheder for, at du kan rykke dig med os, vokse med opgaverne og √•bne nye d√∏re i dit arbejdsliv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4250818671/','2025-06-23',14,NULL,'[\"Administration af IT-infrastruktur\", \"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"Log Analysis\", \"Systemoverv√•gning\"]','2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(84,4257945758,'Founder Residency',63,'Greater Malm√∂ Metropolitan Area','Om jobbet\n\nAbout\n\n\n\n\nReady to build your startup and get funded in 10 weeks? We‚Äôre a global early-stage VC backing founders from day zero. We invest up to ‚Ç¨400k through our founder residency ‚Äì a building sprint where you leverage community, sparring, and intense effort to make 1 year of progress in 10 weeks.\n\n\n\n\nWe have now opened applications for our next Nordics residency starting September 1st, 2025. Build your company alongside a cohort of pre-vetted, exceptional potential co-founders, validate your ideas, engage with customers, develop your MVP, refine your business model, and create your go-to-market strategy before pitching to the investment committee.\n\n\n\n\nAbout You:\n\nWe are looking for Founders, CEOs, CTOs, and others eager to build the next disruptive tech venture from the ground up.\n\nFounder DNA: The residency is built for fully-committed, full-time entrepreneurs (or will go full time by the point of the residency). You know what it means to be a founder and are ready to take it on for the right reasons. Grit, integrity, determination, commitment, humility, and resilience describe you.\nExperience: Successful Antler Founders have a honed skill in addition to Founder DNA. Examples include sales, software development, product design, domain expertise, fundraising, etc. Many worked at startups as founders or employees in the past.\nIndustry Focus: Antler is industry agnostic, as seen in our portfolio of investments. Antler has invested in over 1,500+ companies to date across many industries. In the Nordics, we have an active portfolio size of >150 companies that is well-balanced across different sectors.\n\n\n\n\nThe Antler Founder Residency:\n\nThe residency starts on September 1st, 2025, and runs for 10 weeks, full-time, in-person in Copenhagen. Any adjustments have to be agreed to in the interview process.\n\nOur residency program is fairly unstructured, with 90%+ of the time focused dedicated to founders working on their companies and making week-over-week progress. Here are some examples of things that founders focus on, depending on where they are at in their company journey:\n\n\n\n\nFind and vet potential cofounders\nValidate core assumptions around your business ideas and find meaningful market insight\nBuild prototypes, find design partners, launch pilots, close customers\nGet feedback from functional experts and dedicated coaches\nReach milestones that align with pre-seed funding\n\n\n\n\nIf founders have already accomplished any of the above, they dedicate their full effort on the next most important milestones.\n\n\n\n\nAntler Investment Process\n\nAt the end of the 10-week residency, you will have the opportunity to present to the Antler Investment Committee. If approved by the investment committee, you will receive a pre-seed commitment of ‚Ç¨400,000 in two tranches. ‚Ç¨100k for 10% and ‚Ç¨300k in follow-on capital.\nCompanies that receive investment at the end of the residency will join the Antler portfolio and gain even higher touch programming from our partners. This includes access our network of downstream investors, integration into the Antler Nordics portfolio and global portfolio network, and introductions to relevant partners and discounted service providers.\n\n\n\n\nAbout Antler\n\nAntler is a early-stage VC that is changing the way people build companies. We operate in 30 locations worldwide, have supported 8,000+ founders through our residencies, and invested in 1500+ startups globally. We launched Antler to build a better on-ramp to venture capital. After working in venture-backed companies for years, we built Antler to provide founders with a structured and transparent process to successfully launch a new venture, a community for support throughout the experience, and a clear pathway to venture funding.\n\n\n\n\nAntler Highlights:\n\nSome examples of successful companies that were built as a result of Antler‚Äôs residency, received pre-seed investment from Antler, and have gone on to raise substantial investments are as follows:\n\nAiralo: The world‚Äôs first eSIM subscription and top-up store\nWingbits: Incentive-based flight tracking platform\nTreyd: Working capital operating system for B2B\nReebelo: Used electronics marketplace\nTelgea: Global telecom operator\nGlint Solar: Software for identifying the best solar sites faster\n\n\n\n\nCohort starts: September 1st, 2025\n\n\n\n\nAPPLY NOW','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4257945758/','2025-06-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Start-ups\", \"Erhverv\", \"Finans\", \"Grit\", \"Iv√¶rks√¶tteri\", \"Marketing\", \"Resiliency\", \"Salgsv√¶kst\"]','2025-06-30 11:33:01','2025-06-30 11:33:01'),(85,4239049480,'Bogholder ‚Äì f√• en central rolle i en ambiti√∏s og v√¶rdidrevet virksomhed',64,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nHar du styr p√• debet og kredit, og trives du med ansvar, struktur og pr√¶cision? Hos nofipa ApS s√∏ger vi en erfaren og selvst√¶ndig bogholder, der kan tage ejerskab over vores daglige √∏konomiske drift og v√¶re med til at sikre, at vores regnskaber er i topform.\n\n\n\n\nHvem er vi?\n\nVi er drevet af st√¶rkt k√∏bmandskab og har skabt flere innovative brands og koncepter, der alle er centreret omkring at k√∏be, s√¶lge og levere en h√∏j kundeservice. Vi har forvandlet traditionelle forretningsideer til moderne succeser. Siden vores start i december 2018 har vi udvidet vores tilstedev√¶relse med flere butikker, og du f√•r muligheden for at spille en central rolle i vores sp√¶ndende fremtidige udvikling.\n\nVores mest fremtr√¶dende koncepter in