lementere en ny GEIST-strategi. Din fornemmeste opgave bliver at sikre, at vi kommer godt i m√•l med de inddragende processer og unders√∏gelser p√• tv√¶rs af korpset. Unders√∏gelserne skal munde ud i konkrete handleplaner for det videre arbejde med GEIST til gl√¶de og gavn bredt i korpset.\n\nSom en del af GEIST skal du v√¶re med til at ‚Ä¶\nFacilitere udviklingsm√∏der sammen med frivillige pigespejdere\nSikre og underst√∏tte inddragende processer til at udvikle de tre delindsatser i GEIST: netv√¶rk, viden og unge\nDesigne, gennemf√∏re og evaluere unders√∏gelser (b√•de kvalitative og kvantitative) i korpset, som skal v√¶re med til at forme de konkrete handleplaner\nUnderst√∏tte arbejdet fra indsamling af viden til opstart af unders√∏gelser henimod skabelse af konkrete handleplaner i samarbejde med relevante akt√∏rer hos De gr√∏nne pigespejdere\n\nVi s√∏ger dig, der br√¶nder for at skabe gode samarbejdende processer og er dygtig til at designe og gennemf√∏re kvalitative og kvantitative unders√∏gelser.\n\nVi s√∏ger en proceskonsulent, der b√•de er handlingsorienteret, en dygtig facilitator, og som form√•r at sikre en proaktiv fremdrift i det unders√∏gende arbejde. Er du vores nye proceskonsulent, skal du kunne:\n\nProceslede fra opstart til eksekvering og afslutning\nFacilitere og udvikle i t√¶t samarbejde med frivillige og kollegaer\nDesigne og gennemf√∏re kvalitative og kvantitative unders√∏gelser fra start til slut\nDet praktiske\n\nVi l√¶gger v√¶gt p√•, at du kan fort√¶lle os om, hvordan du konkret ser dine erfaringer omsat hos De gr√∏nne pigespejdere.\n\nStillingen er fuldtid med 37 timers arbejdsuge. Der vil v√¶re arbejde om aftenen og i weekenderne, som processerne kalder p√• det. Stillingen er tidsbegr√¶nset og oph√∏rer 31. marts 2027.\n\nDin prim√¶re arbejdsplads er p√• Korpskontoret i K√∏benhavn (Arsenalvej 10, 1436 K√∏benhavn K).\n\nI din ans√¶ttelse vil du referere til De gr√∏nne pigespejderes generalsekret√¶r, Winnie Berndtson.\n\nAns√∏gningsfrist\n\nD. 1. august 2025 kl. 12.00. Ans√∏gning og CV sendes som √©n samlet PDF-fil til job@pigespejder.dk. Skriv ‚ÄúProceskonsulent GEIST‚Äù i emnefeltet.\n\nVi afholder samtaler i uge 34.\n\nHar du sp√∏rgsm√•l til stillingen, er du velkommen til at kontakte Organisationskonsulent og projektleder p√• GEIST Maria Jakobsen p√• mja@pigespejder.dk eller 81885233.\n\nL√¶s mere om De gr√∏nne pigespejdere p√• www.pigespejder.dk','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248415454/','2025-06-16',15,NULL,'[\"Business process improvement\", \"Coaching\", \"Facilitering\", \"Forretningsadministration\", \"IT-serviceadministration\", \"ITIL\", \"Procesforbedring\", \"Procesoptimering\", \"Samarbejde\", \"Six Sigma\"]','2025-06-30 11:36:41','2025-06-30 11:36:41'),(124,4252996052,'Automation Engineer',97,'Skovlunde, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nOn behalf ot our client: B√ºhler Denmark A/S\n\nWe are seeking a candidate to fill an Automation Engineer role. \nYour background needs to include some experience with PLC programming, whether you are newly graduated or have a couple of years of experience and want to grow and learn more.\nYou will work with high-end industrial baking equipment, designing PLC and HMI control systems for oven lines, conveyor systems, dough feeding systems, depositors, and other equipment.\n\n\n\n\nAbout B√ºhler\n\nEvery day, billions of people come into contact with B√ºhler technologies to cover their basic needs for food and mobility. We strive for innovations for a better world, focusing on healthy, safe, sustainable solutions. We contribute significantly to feeding the world‚Äôs population while setting the focus on food security and safety. Our solutions and technologies enable efficient and clean mobility.\n\n\n\n\nAs a leading technology group, B√ºhler invests up to 5% of its yearly turnover in research and development. In 2022, around 12,700 employees in over 140 countries generated a turnover of CHF 3.0 billion. As a globally active Swiss family-owned company, we are committed to sustainability. We want our customers to be successful. We want every human being to have access to healthy food. We want to protect the climate with energy-efficient cars, buildings, and machinery.\n\n\n\n\nB√ºhler Denmark A/S\n\n\n\n\nB√ºhler Denmark A/S and Business Unit (BU) is an independent manufacturer and distributor of high-end baking machinery.\n\nThe Biscuit Unit is part of the Grains & Food Division of the B√ºhler Group. The BU has 191 employees, with HQ in Skovlunde/Copenhagen and a Manufacturing Site in R√∏dk√¶rsbro for highly specialized tunnel ovens (63 employees).\n\nOur machines, typically delivered within 6 months of customer orders, are based on standard machinery but very often undergo customization. This provides technical challenges as we tailor solutions to meet specific customer needs making our jobs technically challenging and exciting.\n\n\n\n\nB√ºhler has an Application & Training Center in Skovlunde HQ, a collaborative platform to inspire and innovate. It is also where customers can test machinery and experiment with recipes on demonstration lines.\n\n\n\n\nThe position\n\n\n\n\nWe are seeking an Automation Engineer to make and implement control systems for our high-end baking machinery. This includes oven control for tunnel ovens and dough handling related to our customers‚Äô projects.\n\nThe equipment and solutions are delivered worldwide, and you will work closely with the other engineers in the team, the project managers, and other departments. You will also be in close contact with the company‚Äôs customers and Buhler\'s other production sites.\n\nFor each project, you must create software for a fully functional control system that the installation department can install and commission with minimal support from your side. All production and assembly is carried out from Austria (Leobendorf).\n\nWe are working towards having more standardized software that is quicker and easier to scale.\n\nYou will be part of our Automation team in Skovlunde, which is part of the Electrical and automation department, which covers teams in Skovlunde, R√∏dk√¶rsbro (Jutland), and Leobendorf (Austria).\n\nYou will refer to the Department Head of Engineering, based in Skovlunde.\n\n\n\n\nThere is some traveling to Leobendorf and customers, with flexibility to fit your schedule.\n\n\n\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n\n\n\nDesign of PLC and HMI control systems for oven lines, conveyor systems, dough feeding systems, depositors, and other equipment\nSet up the industrial network, frequency converters, servo drives, etc.\nSystems test at the office in Skovlunde\nSupport for customers and field engineers across the globe\nCommissioning of custom-engineered machines\nCollaboration with the company\'s other departments, both in Denmark and abroad, in connection with the production of large baking lines\nTravel to customers and Buhler Group manufacturing sites\n\n\n\n\nThe ideal candidate\n\n\n\n\nThe ideal candidate is interested in working in a more traditional machinery-building industry or already has experience. Our systems and designs are more open and flexible, perhaps more grounded in the real world where you can taste the product!\n\n\n\n\nYou should be interested in close involvement with our customers, who often require tailored solutions. We are working with new technologies in oven design and state-of-the-art electric-powered ovens. So, having ideas and being creative is welcomed in this role. You should be able to think out of the box and enjoy different tasks and a broader role depending on your profile and experience.\n\n\n\n\nCandidate qualifications \n\n\n\n\nHold a relevant education, such as electrical automation engineer (BSc/BEng) or engineer (Maskinmester) or Automationsteknolog\nSome experience in PLC programs using Ladder Logic and Structured Text\nSome experience with HMI an advantage\nCapable of interpreting electrical schematics to support PLC programming and troubleshooting\nKnowledge of PLCs ; our primary systems are Allen Bradley and Siemens\nA general interest in the mechanical components of machinery and interest for servo systemsis Knowledge of standards such as EN 60204-1 and EN 13849 is an advantage\nKnowledge of the food industry is an advantage, but not a requirement\nFluent in both spoken and written English\nLiving in the Copenhagen area with a valid work and resident permit\n\nPrepared for some travel activity in connection with customer visits and commissioning as well as meetings in other of the group‚Äôs companies.\n\n\n\n\nWhy you should join the B√ºhler Group\n\n\n\n\nYou will be part of the B√ºhler Group.\n\nWork with high-end machinery for biscuit and cracker production company with short decision-making paths n environment where mechanical engineers, automation specialists, and R&D teams work closely together\nGood international career possibilities\nPossibility to influence the role\nFlexible working time\nGet in touch with our B√ºhler Spirit.\nBrand new offices and a great canteen\nHealth insurance.\nAnd finally, several committed colleagues.\n\n\n\n\nFor more information\n\n\n\n\nFor more information, do not hesitate to get in touch with Partner Anne Borgen at anne@peoplement.dk or by phone at +45 6169 01 01','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4252996052/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\"Allen-Bradley\", \"PLC-programmering\"]','2025-06-30 11:36:41','2025-06-30 11:36:41'),(125,4249645320,'Ny kollega i en koordinerende rolle med de nyeste teknologier indenfor Core Infrastruktur i Danmarks st√∏rste offentlige sundhedsteknologiske virksomhed',98,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nVil du arbejde i en koordinerende rolle med de nyeste teknologier indenfor Core Infrastruktur i Danmarks st√∏rste offentlige sundhedsteknologiske virksomhed? Og vil du bruge dine evner inden for teknologiomr√•det Windows til at sikre effektiv og stabil drift, der er med til at redde liv? \n\nSammen med b√•de sundhedsfag