nes, and security protocols.\nRecruit, manage, and mentor the engineering team.\nServe as the technical face of the company in conversations with partners, auditors, and investors.\n\n\n\n\nRequired Skills & Experience\n\n5+ years of software engineering experience, including 2+ years in the blockchain/crypto space.\nProven expertise in Golang, with experience architecting backend systems from the ground up.\nAdvanced knowledge of Solidity and deep familiarity with the EVM, including proxy patterns and upgradeable contracts.\nHands-on experience with development tools like Hardhat, Foundry, Ethers.js, and OpenZeppelin.\nExperience building systems that connect on-chain smart contracts with off-chain services (compliance, custody, payments).\nStrong understanding of token standards (ERC-20, ERC-4626), stablecoin designs, and cross-chain infrastructure.\nEntrepreneurial mindset: action-oriented, low-ego, and comfortable in early-stage environments.\n\n\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nDirect experience launching or scaling fiat-backed stablecoins or tokenized payment systems.\nBackground in fintech, crypto custody, or regulated financial infrastructure.\nFamiliarity with L2 ecosystems, zero-knowledge proofs, cross-chain bridges, or account abstraction.\nOpen-source contributions to blockchain or developer infrastructure projects.\n\n\n\n\nBenefits & Perks\n\nCompetitive salary plus significant founding equity stake.\nFully remote with flexible work arrangements (US/EU time zones preferred).\nOpportunity to join a world-class team from Circle and Coinbase.\nInfluence the architecture of a critical financial infrastructure platform.\nWork on a zero-to-one product with massive potential in the digital asset space.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259415838/','2025-06-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Betalingssystemer\", \"Blockchain\", \"Ethereum\", \"Infrastructure Projects\", \"Smart Contracts\"]','2025-06-30 11:44:53','2025-06-30 11:44:53'),(204,4257965678,'Frontend Engineer [3