r i skolen, direkte i din hverdag i butikken.\n\nP√• skolen tr√¶ner du salg, pr√¶sentationsteknik, √∏konomi og markedsf√∏ring, s√• du bliver dygtig til at levere verdens bedste kundeoplevelse. Du vil derfor ogs√• opleve, at du hurtigt bidrager til dit team og i butikken.\n\nSend din ans√∏gning i dag ‚Äì vi gl√¶der os til at l√¶re dig at kende!\n\nAns√∏gningsfrist: 1. juli 2025\n\nStartdato: Senest 01/09/2025\n\nArbejdssted: Slotsarkaderne 34, Hiller√∏d 3400 DNK\n\nLeder i butikken: Anders Leander Pedersen - mail: anlpe@yousee.dk\n\nNuuday ‚Äì We make sense with technology\n\nHos Nudaay er vi 3.000 dedikerede medarbejdere, der p√• tv√¶rs af vores seks brands ‚Äì YouSee, TDC Erhverv, Telmore, Hiper, eesy og Relatel ‚Äì arbejder m√•lrettet p√• at s√¶tte retningen for Danmarks digitale fremtid. Vi befinder os midt i en sp√¶ndende transformation, hvor vi ikke blot revolutionerer vores IT-systemer, men ogs√• skaber innovative digitale kundeoplevelser, der s√¶tter nye standarder for, hvordan danskere, virksomheder og samfundet interagerer med teknologi i hverdagen. Hos Nuuday finder du en kultur pr√¶get af mangfoldighed, samarbejde og udvikling. Uanset hvor du arbejder, eller hvilket brand du er en del af, er √©n ting f√¶lles for os alle: en passion for at skabe l√∏sninger, der g√∏r en forskel. Vi s√¶tter en √¶re i at forst√• vores\n\nkunder, og vi ser fremtiden som en mulighed for konstant at udvikle og forbedre os. Vi tror p√•, at et st√¶rkt f√¶llesskab l√¶gger fundamentet til store resultater, og hos os er der altid plads til dem, der t√∏r t√¶nke nyt, tage ansvar og v√¶re med til at bane vejen. Vil du v√¶re med?\n\n#YouSee','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4089774104/','2025-06-16',13,NULL,'[\"Styresystemer\", \"Driftsledelse\", \"Events\", \"HF\", \"Katastrofemedicin\"]','2025-06-30 11:46:39','2025-06-30 11:46:39'),(231,4099920628,'ServiceNow Senior Consultant, Denmark',162,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nServiceNow Senior Consultant at the leading European HR Digital Transformation Partner\n\nAbout The Role\n\nWe are seeking an experienced and innovative ServiceNow Senior Consultant to join our team. The team you‚Äôll be joining is highly skilled and ambitious ‚Äì just as you are ‚Äì and together we will bring world-class employee experiences to life, in some of the most exciting organization in the world. We strive to be the best.\n\nA significant part of Gavdi¬¥s focus is on cutting-edge HR solutions, such as ServiceNow HRSD and SAP SuccessFactors. You will play an essential role in designing and implementing ServiceNow for HR, ensuring our customers fully benefit from combining ServiceNow with SuccessFactors, Workday and other HR-solutions. We also help our customers across the ServiceNow platform, including ITSM, CSM, IRM/TPRM, Integration Hub and Automation Engine, and continuously expand our services matching the growth of ServiceNow. Together with the international Gavdi team you will deliver the next generation of Cloud applications and services to our clients.\n\nWhat You‚Äôll Do\n\n\nImplementation Leadership: Lead design and configuration for ServiceNow implementation projects, utilizing NowCreate with design thinking and best practice process design methodologies.\nPre-Sales Support: Assist in preparing and delivering pre-sales demonstrations, showcasing the value and capabilities of ServiceNow to potential clients.\nClient Engagement: Participate in customer events sharing best practices and success stories to support client understanding and adoption of ServiceNow solutions.\nPlatform Expertise: Maintain deep knowledge of ServiceNow‚Äôs advanced capabilities and how they are practically used.\nInnovation And Development: Engage in innovation initiatives, developing new features and enhancements that leverage ServiceNow‚Äôs platform capabilities to meet evolving customer needs.\n\n\nWho You Are\n\nYou‚Äôre naturally curious and motivated by helping your clients solve problems based on modern technology. You understand the impact of process improvements and innovation on employee experience, and you want to become the natural trusted advisor to business and technology leaders. Additionally, you‚Äôre a natural team-player, and you thrive in a dynamic environment.\n\nAs we‚Äôre looking for ServiceNow senior consultants, we‚Äôd prefer that you have:\n\n\nBachelor‚Äôs degree or higher in relevant field.\nExperience working in a consultancy environment.\n3+ year‚Äôs of experience implementing ServiceNow.\n2+ year¬¥s of ‚Äúhands on‚Äù-experience implementing ServiceNow HRSD.\nActive certification in ServiceNow HR (ServiceNow HR-CIS; ideally also Pro and related training and certification).\nExperience working efficiently with remote teams and customers.\nAbility to handle multiple projects/tasks simultaneously, meet deadlines, while effectively managing priorities. and communicating progress.\nNative Danish speaker. Excellent spoken and written English.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4099920628/','2024-12-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"JavaScript\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Design Thinking\", \"Handle Multiple Projects\", \"IT-serviceadministration\", \"Pre-Sales Support\", \"Probleml√∏sning\", \"Produktdemonstration\", \"Pr√¶-salg\", \"ServiceNow\"]','2025-06-30 11:47:15','2025-06-30 11:47:15'),(232,4257955362,'Quality Assurance Student',163,'Kongens Lyngby, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nStart your career as a Student Assistant for Quality Management\n\nAre you passionate about the development and optimization of processes in our Quality Management System so they ensure the entire organisation can connect the future of satellite communication? Do you enjoy a collaborative and diverse working environment? Do you want to further develop your skills with highly specialised colleagues who are willing to let you learn from the best? Then we encourage you to read on.\n\n\n\n\nYour key responsibilities will involve:\n\nAs our student worker, you will play a key role in improving our Quality Management System and supporting the work with ensuring that the business complies with regulatory standards. We are looking for a new student worker, who ‚Äì amongst other things - will:\n\nCollaborate with various stakeholders to map and document processes in the organizational Quality Management Software (Qualiware).\nOptimize existing processes to ensure clarity and alignment towards regulatory standards.\n Collect, analyse, and visualize Quality data.\nSupport the Quality Team with various projects and ad-hoc tasks.\n\n\n\n\nYour skills and qualifications will preferably include:\n\nCurrently studying a relevant Masters‚Äô Degree in a technical or commercial field, e.g., Industrial Management, Design and Innovation, or Business Administration.\nThat you know your way around the Microsoft Office package including PowerPoint, Excel, and Word.\nPrevious experience in working with regulatory standards is an advantage, more importantly that you are interested in learning more.\n\n\n\n\nYou will enjoy this job if you:\n\nHave a mindset of continuous improvement ‚Äì one of the cornerstones of quality management is to always seek opportunities to do things better. If you have an urge in constantly develop yourself and your environment, this is the right place for you.\nHave strong communication skills (both written and spoken) in English ‚Äì Danish is a plus but not necessary ‚Äì as you will collaborate with many different stakeholders in the organization, it is crucial that you feel confident in reaching out and talking to your colleagues. \nEnjoy overcoming complex challenges ‚Äì the job offers many exciting challenges, which are not always easy to fix. Therefore, creative problem solving must be something that comes naturally to you.\n\n\n\n\nWe estimate that you will be working between 15-20 hours/week.\n\n\n\n\nBeing a student worker at Cobham Satcom\n\nAt Cobham Satcom, you‚Äôll also benefit from a large, vibrant and active student network, with numerous events held throughout the year. This provides you with plenty of opportunities to connect, learn, and socialize with peers from diverse backgrounds, helping you grow both professionally and personally.\n\n\n\n\nApplication\n\nDoes this sound like the exciting challenge you have been looking for? Then please submit your resume and a short cover letter. Note you can only upload a single file so please include all the above in a merged document. \n\n\n\n\nWant to know more?\n\nIf you have any further questions about the Student Worker position, please contact Albert Bronstein by phone +45 29 94 83 06 or e-mail: albert.bronstein@cobhamsatcom.com.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4257955362/','2025-06-30',5,NULL,'[\"Engelsk\", \"Microsoft Office\", \"Dataanalyse\", \"Dataindtastning\", \"Kreativ probleml√∏sning\", \"Kvalitetskontrol\", \"Kvalitetssikring\", \"Kvalitetssystem\", \"Overholdelse af myndighedskrav\", \"Regulatory Standards\"]','2025-06-30 11:47:15','2025-06-30 11:47:15'),(233,4239035286,'S4HANA QM Analyst',164,'Den Europ√¶iske Union','Om jobbet\n\nDecskill was founded in 2014 as an IT Consulting Company and their main mission is to delivery value through the knowledge. We enable companies to meet the chalenges of digital world by providing our clients with business models that ensure technological capacity, flexibility and agility. We are more than 500 consultants with offices in Lisbon, Porto and Madrid.\n\n\n\n\nDECSKILL operates in 3 main areas:\n\n\n\n\n‚Ä¢ DECSKILL TALENT, through which we provide our clients with an extension to their IT teams;\n\n‚Ä¢ DECSKILL BOOST, through which we provide our client with software development models to increase capacity and optimize Time-to-Market, where we create and manage teams that deliver according to their needs, at the desired speed;\n\n‚Ä¢ DECSKILL CONNECT, through which we provide our client with consulting services, as well as the implementation and management of information technology infrastructures.\n\n\n\n\nOur practice results in the creation of value for our customers, either by delivering qualified and value-added services, or through highly qualified and motivated professionals, as well as technology solutions that allow us to operate and transform the business of our customers.\n\n\n\n\nWe are looking for a S4HANA QM Analyst for a remote project in Europe.\n\n\n\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n\n\n\n Translate requirements into SAP topics configuration;\n Perform detail analysis of complex business process requirements and propose solutions;\n Build and Unit Test the functional solution into SAP;\n Keep the project documentation updated ( Design Documents, Process Flows, configuration document etc.);\n Create functional design specifications (FDS) and support developers on the creation of the technical design specifications (TDS);\n Provide support to global data standards definition, cleansing and migration Support E2E testing activities (testing documentation, data and other prerequisites) and the resolution of testing defects;\n Drive workshops\n\n\n\n\nEssential Skills: \n\n\n\n\n Extensive experience with SAP QM and good understanding of the integration between QM and the other modules of S4HANA, namely PP-PI, EWM, IM, SD and PM\n Hands on experience in the key SAP S/4 functionalities QM ideally in pharma environment\n Strong analytical & problem-solving skills\n Experienced with Client relations/Stakeholder management\n Excellent interpersonal, oral and written communication\nGood English communication skills\n\n\n\n\nIf you‚Äôre interested in this job please send your CV in English to daniela.adao@decskill.com with reference ‚ÄúDA/QM‚Äù.\n\n\n\n\nDecskill is committed to equality and non-discrimination with all our talents. We recruit and promote talent, based on diversity and inclusion, regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, race, nationality or any other form of discrimination incompatible with the dignity of the human being.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4239035286/','2025-06-02',56,NULL,'[\"Engelsk\", \"Linux\", \"SQL\", \"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"Forretningsadministration\", \"ITIL\", \"Klientrelationer\", \"Kommunikation\", \"SAP\", \"Skriftlig kommunikation\"]','2025-06-30 11:47:15','2025-06-30 11:47:15');
